Merchandise Planning Business Analyst - PT Courts Retail Indonesia
Merchandise Planning Business Analyst  -
Merchandise Planning Business Analyst
Responsibilities
Analysis responsibilities include monitoring store category sales, supervising physical inventory, identifying trends, and monitoring the timing and scope of seasonal changesAllocation responsibilities include maintaining desired inventory levels and assortments, scheduling deliveries, and overseeing shipping/receiving and warehousing of merchandise.Working directly with suppliers, merchandising analysts develop supply strategies that will minimize stockouts while maximizing inventory turnsset up items for replenishment, forecast and order product, allocate it to the right stores based on their sales patterns, and make a smooth operational and supply chainDelivering business growth in terms of net sales, operating profit, and cash conversion cycle from Finance standpoint, including the analysis, planning, and management reporting.Industry research about competitorsAlign with Buyer/merchandiser about product development and improvement and product costPreparation of monthly and ad-hoc reporting to support the sales, marketing, and product teamsCompletion of month end process including P&L and balance sheet review ensuring revenue recognition, provisions and other accounting adjustments are in line with accounting policies and reflect business performanceCandidate must possess at least a Bachelor's Degree, any field.Required skill(s): merchandising, analysis, Planning And Inventory Control.At least 5 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.Preferably Manager / Assistant Managers specializing in Merchandising or equivalent.Full-Time position(s) available.
